'''Ibn al-Fuwati''' (1244&ndash;1323) (Arabic: ابن الفوطي) was an [[Iraq]]i historian who wrote a great deal, but whose works have mostly been lost. Large portions of his biographical dictionary ''Madjma' al-adab fi mu'djam al-alqab''. He was active in Iraq and [[Azerbaijan]], and his most famous teaching position was at the [[Mustansiriya School|Madrasa Mustansiriya]].
