'''María del Pilar León-Castro Alonso''' ([[Seville]], 13 September 1946) is a Spanish archaeologist and historian, as well as an academician of the [[Real Academia de la Historia]].
In 1969, León-Castro Alonso graduated in arts from the [[University of Seville]] with honors and received her doctorate there in 1974. She studied under [[Antonio Blanco Freijeiro]], and extended her studies in [[Bonn]] by a grant from the [[Alexander von Humboldt Foundation]]. She also spent two years conducting research at the Institute of Archaeology Rodrigo Caro [[Spanish National Research Council]].<ref name="europapress">{{cite web|title=El cantante de Supersubmarina, operado de urgencia y el batería, en estado grave tras un accidente de coche|url=http://www.europapress.es/cultura/noticia-pilar-leon-castro-alonso-nueva-academica-real-academia-historia-20120413201136.html|publisher=Europa Press|accessdate=16 August 2016|location=Madrid|language=Spanish}}</ref> Her research has included Roman [[Córdoba, Andalusia|Córdoba]]. Previously a professor at the [[Complutense University of Madrid]], the [[University of Santiago de Compostela]], the [[University of Córdoba (Spain)|University of Cordoba]], and the [[University Pablo de Olavide]], she is currently a professor of archeology at the University of Seville.<ref name="us.es">{{cite web|title=LEON-CASTRO ALONSO, MARIA DEL PILAR|url=http://www.us.es/acerca/directorio/ppdi/personal_9573|publisher=University of Seville|accessdate=16 August 2016|language=Spanish}}</ref>
León-Castro Alonso founded the magazine ''Romula'' which focuses on the archeology of Roman ruins in the [[Iberian Peninsula]]. She is a member of the [[German Archaeological Institute]] and an academic of the Real Academia de Bellas Artes de Santa Isabel de Hungría. León-Castro Alonso was elected to ''medalla nº 9'' of the [[Real Academia de la Historia]] on 13 April 2012; she took up her seat on 19 May 2013.<ref name="rah.es">{{cite web|title=DOÑA MARÍA DEL PILAR LEÓN-CASTRO ALONSO NUEVA ACADÉMICA DE NÚMERO DE LA REAL ACADEMIA DE LA HISTORIA|url=http://www.rah.es/pdf/Eleccion_Pilar_Leon.pdf|publisher=Real Academia de la Historia|accessdate=16 August 2016|language=Spanish|format=PDF}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.rah.es/da-ma-del-pilar-leon-castro-alonso/ |title=Mª Del Pilar León-Castro Alonso |language=Spanish |publisher=Real Academia de la Historia |date= |accessdate=24 December 2016}}</ref>
